Package com.pandora.general.logic

package com.pandora.general.logic
Provides classes and interfaces related to general logic in the context of freshwater biogeochemistry within the Pandora project.

The classes in this package include logic implementations for sediment transport coefficients and shear stress calculations, crucial in understanding erosion and sedimentation processes in freshwater ecosystems.

This package follows the Spring Framework's convention and includes Spring components, such as Component annotated classes, for integration into larger applications that leverage dependency injection and component scanning.

The key interfaces in this package are:

  • ErosionLogic
  • ShearStressLogic
These interfaces define methods for calculating sediment transport coefficients and shear stress parameters relevant to freshwater biogeochemistry studies.
  • Class
    Description
    ErosionLogic
    The ErosionLogic interface defines a method for calculating the sediment transport coefficient based on specified erosion-related parameters.
    ErosionLogicImpl
    The ErosionLogicImpl class is an implementation of the ErosionLogic interface, providing a method to calculate the sediment transport coefficient based on specified parameters.
    ShearStressLogic
    The ShearStressLogic interface defines methods for calculating shear stress, critical shear stress for sediment transport, and the Shields parameter based on specified parameters.
    ShearStressLogicImpl
    The ShearStressLogicImpl class is an implementation of the ShearStressLogic interface, providing methods to calculate shear stress, critical shear stress for sediment transport, and the Shields parameter based on specified parameters.
